TY  - JOUR
AU  - Boehmer, Ekkehart
AU  - Huszár, Zsuzsa R
AU  - Wang, Yanchu
AU  - Zhang, Xiaoyan
AU  - Zhang, Xinran
T1  - Can Shorts Predict Returns? A Global Perspective
PY  - 2022
Y1  - 2022/05/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhab079
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 35
IS  - 5
SP  - 2428
EP  - 2463
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Using multiple short-sale measures, we examine the predictive power of short sales for future stock returns in 38 countries from July 2006 to December 2014. We find that the days-to-cover ratio and the utilization ratio measures have the most robust predictive power for future stock returns in the global capital market. Our results display significant cross-country and cross-firm differences in the predictive power of alternative short-sale measures. The predictive power of shorts is stronger in countries with nonprohibitive short sale regulations and for stocks with relatively low liquidity, high shorting fees, and low price efficiency.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhab079
ER  - 



